20University%20and%20an%20author%20on%20the%20study%2C%20said%20in%20a%20post%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fmercury-shrinking-planet-is-still-getting-smaller-new-research-213675%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20like%20the%20wrinkles%20that%20form%20on%20an%20apple%20as%20it%20ages%2C%26quot%3B%20Rothery%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20used%20these%20scarps%20to%20prove%20the%20planet%20has%20shrunk.%20The%20problem%20is%20most%20of%20these%20are%20ancient%20%E2%80%94%20about%203%20billion%20years%20old%2C%20Rothery%20told%20Insider%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20show%20that%20these%20scarps%20are%20still%20moving%20today%2C%20Rothery%20and%20his%20graduate%20student%20Ben%20Man%20turned%20their%20attention%20to%20another%20geological%20structure%2C%20called%20grabens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20advantage%20of%20these%20grabens%2C%20which%20appear%20as%20the%20scarps%20move%20about%2C%20is%20that%20they%20are%20quite%20slight%2C%20only%20about%200.6%20miles%20long%20and%20under%20300%20feet%20deep.%20They%20don't%20last%20as%20long%20%E2%80%94%20any%20older%20than%20300%20million%20years%20would%20probably%20no%20longer%20be%20visible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20there%20are%20such%20small%20structures%2C%20they%20wouldn't%20survive%20for%20very%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20Rothery%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20published%20in%20Nature%20Geosciences%20on%20Monday%2C%20identified%2048%20definite%20and%20244%20likely%20grabens%20on%20pictures%20snapped%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwatch-messenger-collide-with-mercury-2015-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA's%20MESSENGER%20probe%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222460%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Symbols%20scattered%20about%20ta%20map%20of%20Mercury%20shows%20the%20location%20of%20grabens%20on%20the%20surface.%20These%20are%20mostly%20shown%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bprobable%26quot%3B%20though%20some%20show%20up%20as%20%26quot%3Bdefinite.%26quot%3B%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651c0ac2617692f0d03d68fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221042%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20map%20shows%20the%20location%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bdefinite%26quot%3B%20grabens%20(yellow%20triangles)%20and%20%26quot%3Bprobable%26quot%3B%20grabens%20(black%20circles)%20identified%20by%20Rothery%20and%20his%20co-authors%20on%20Mercury.%3Cp%3EMan%2C%20B.%2C%20Rothery%2C%20D.A.%2C%20Balme%2C%20M.R.%20et%20al.%20Nat.%20Geosci.%20(2023).%20https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1038%2Fs41561-023-01281-5%2C%20CC-BY%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20why%20we%20say%20clearly%20there's%20been%20some%20movement%20in%20about%20the%20past%20three%20hundred%20million%20years%2C%20and%20it's%20probably%20going%20on%20today%20still%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMercury%20is%20likely%20constantly%20shaking%20with%20quakes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20also%20suggests%20Mercury%20is%20constantly%20shaking%20with%20quakes%2C%20Rothery%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20Mercury%20is%20shrinking%2C%20you're%20causing%20bits%20of%20the%20outer%20rigid%20part%20to%20be%20thrust%20over%20itself.%20So%20that%20is%20an%20earthquake%20%E2%80%94%20or%20a%20Mercury%20quake%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20quakes%20are%20likely%20quite%20big%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20displacement%20we%20see%20on%20these%20fronts%20is%20a%20couple%20of%20kilometres.%20So%20that's%20hundreds%20of%20really%2C%20really%20big%20earthquakes%2C%20and%20likely%20millions%20of%20smaller%20ones.%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20expect%20that%20it's%20going%20on%20all%20the%20time%2C%20but%20we've%20got%20no%20way%20of%20measuring%20them%20until%20we%20get%20some%20seismometers%20onto%20the%20planet%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20picture%20of%20Mercury%20taken%20by%20Bepi%20columbo%20is%20shown%20here.%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651c0bc5617692f0d03d6a56%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20photo%20from%20BepiColombo's%20first%20Mercury%20flyby%20on%20October%201%2C%202021.%3Cp%3EESA%2FBepiColombo%2FMTM%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%203.0%20IGO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20step%20for%20Mercury%2C%20Rothery%20said%2C%20will%20be%20the%20arrival%20of%20a%20space%20probe%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbepicolombo-spacecraft-snaps-flies-past-mercury-craters-photos-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBepiColumbo%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Launched%20in%202018%2C%20BepiColumbo%20carries%20two%20satellites%3A%20one%20from%20the%20European%20Space%20Agency%20and%20one%20from%20the%20Japan%20Aerospace%20Exploration%20Agency%2C%20that%20will%20be%20scrutinising%20the%20planet's%20surface%20from%20different%20angles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20probe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbepicolombo-spacecraft-snaps-flies-past-mercury-craters-photos-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etook%20a%20picture%20of%20Mercury%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20flying%20by%20the%20planet%20in%202021%2C%20but%20it%20is%20due%20to%20return%20to%20take%20higher-resolution%20pictures%20in%20late%202025%2C%20early%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hope%20is%20that%20these%20pictures%20could%20provide%20even%20more%20information%20about%20Mercury's%20geology%2C%20for%20instance%20by%20revealing%20boulder%20tracks%20in%20the%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20see%20boulders%20bouncing%20down%20the%20front%20of%20a%20scarps%20or%20the%20boulder%20tracks%20in%20front%20of%20these%20scarps%2C%20you%20might%20think%20well%2C%20maybe%20that's%20the%20Mercury%20quake%20that's%20dislodged%20