%20making%20it%20the%20worst%20performing%20sector%20of%202023%20so%20far.%20The%20sector%20was%20down%205%25%20alone%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sharp%20decline%20has%20come%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-rate-hike-july-inflation-powell-recession-federal-reserve-2023-7%5C%22%3Eamid%20an%20ongoing%20rise%20in%20interest%20rates%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%2010-year%20US%20Treasury%20yield%20jumping%20from%203.75%25%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year%20to%204.73%25%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20have%20often%20flocked%20to%20utility%20stocks%20during%20periods%20of%20market%20and%20economic%20stress%20because%20of%20their%20high%20dividend%20yields%2C%20but%20that%20allure%20has%20faded%20now%20that%20cash%20offers%20a%20risk-free%20return%20of%20about%205%25.%20The%20Utilities%20Select%20Sector%20SPDR%20ETF%20currently%20offers%20a%20dividend%20yield%20of%203.77%25%2C%20which%20is%20more%20than%20double%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fs%26amp%3Bp_500%5C%22%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500's%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A01.50%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20have%20utility%20dividend%20yields%20often%20outpaced%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%2C%20but%20they've%20also%20been%20higher%20than%20bonds%20for%20nearly%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20average%20monthly%20yield%20for%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20Utilities%20sector%20since%20December%202004%20was%203.3%25%20versus%20the%20average%2010-year%20yield%20of%202.8%25%2C%26quot%3B%20CFRA%20Research%20chief%20equity%20strategist%20Sam%20Stovall%20told%20Insider%20on%20Monday.%20Today%2C%20investors%20can%20get%20one%20full%20percentage%20point%20more%20in%20yield%20from%20Treasury%20bonds%20than%20from%20utility%20stocks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sector%20is%20also%20defensive%20because%20utilities%20usually%20have%20regional%20monopolies%2C%20with%20regulators%20often%20granting%20them%20small%20price%20increases%20over%20a%20multiyear%20time%20frame%2C%20allowing%20for%20low%20but%20steady%20growth.%20And%20during%20periods%20of%20economic%20stress%2C%20consumers'%20top%20priority%20is%20to%20pay%20their%20monthly%20utility%20bill%20to%20keep%20the%20lights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20a%20period%20of%20stellar%20outperformance%20in%202022%2C%20when%20the%20sector%20was%20down%20just%201%25%20compared%20to%20the%2019%25%20decline%20seen%20in%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%2C%20that%20has%20completely%20unraveled.%20Since%20the%20start%20of%202022%2C%20the%20utility%20sector%20is%20down%2022%25%20compared%20to%20a%2010%25%20decline%20for%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20that%20has%20to%20do%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20utility%20companies%20rely%20on%20a%20lot%20of%20debt%20to%20fund%20their%20operations%20and%20build%20out%20their%20energy%20production%20capacity%2C%20upgrade%20their%20grid%2C%20and%20improve%20their%20reliability.%20And%20all%20that%20debt%2C%20most%20of%20which%20was%20financed%20during%20a%20period%20of%20near-zero%20rates%2C%20is%20set%20to%20add%20to%20costs%20once%20utilities%20take%20on%20new%20debt%20or%20refinance%20existing%20debt%20at%20higher%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20debt-to-equity%20ratios%20of%20the%20three%20biggest%20utility%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fnee-stock%5C%22%3ENextEra%20Energy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fso-stock%5C%22%3ESouthern%20Company%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fduk-stock%5C%22%3EDuke%20Energy%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20are%20all%20elevated%20relative%20to%20other%20sectors%2C%20currently%20between%201.6x%20and%202.0x.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20regulated%20nature%20of%20utilities%20limits%20their%20ability%20to%20pass%20those%20higher%20rate-related%20costs%20on%20to%20consumers%20as%20they%20have%20to%20get%20ap