und%20during%20the%20raids.%20They%20were%20also%20carrying%20a%20list%20of%2020-25%20questions%20-%20on%20protests%20by%20farmers%20against%20the%20Modi%20government's%20%26quot%3Bblack%26quot%3B%20farm%20laws%20and%20protests%20in%20Delhi's%20Shaheen%20Bagh%20against%20the%20citizenship%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20against%20NewsClick%20and%20journalists%20linked%20to%20the%20website%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnewsclick-raids-enforcement-directorate-china-38-crore-funding-case-explained-5-anti-terror-law-2-criminal-code-sections-in-newsclick-case-4445291%5C%22%3Echarges%20%3C%2Fa%3Eunder%20five%20sections%20of%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20and%20two%20under%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20charges%20include%20criminal%20conspiracy%2C%20promoting%20enmity%20between%20different%20groups%2C%20terrorist%20act%20and%20raising%20funds%20for%20terrorist%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPress%20organisations%20have%20expressed%20concern%20over%20the%20crackdown%20against%20NewsClick.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20said%20in%20a%20statement%2C%20%26quot%3BEGI%20is%20deeply%20concerned%20about%20the%20raids%20at%20the%20residences%20of%20senior%20journalists%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20October%203%2C%20and%20the%20subsequent%20detention%20of%20many%20of%20those%20journalists.%20Urges%20the%20state%20to%20follow%20due%20process%2C%20and%20not%20to%20make%20draconian%20criminal%20laws%20as%20tools%20for%20press%20intimidation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Press%20Club%20of%20India%20put%20out%20a%20statement%20with%20a%20hashtag%20%23DefendMediaFreedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Press%20Club%20Of%20India%20is%20deeply%20concerned%20about%20the%20multiple%20raids%20conducted%20on%20the%20houses%20of%20journalists%20and%20writers%20associated%20with%20Newsclick.%20We%20are%20monitoring%20the%20developments%20and%20will%20be%20releasing%20a%20detailed%20statement%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnion%20Minister%20Anurag%20Thakur%20told%20reporters%20in%20Bhubaneswar%20that%20he%20doesn't%20need%20to%20justify%20the%20action%20by%20security%20agencies.%20%26quot%3BIf%20anyone%20has%20committed%20anything%20wrong%2C%20search%20agencies%20are%20free%20to%20carry%20out%20investigations%20against%20them%20under%20set%20guidelines%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Opposition%20parties%20have%20hit%20out%20at%20the%20government%20over%20the%20raids.%20The%20INDIA%20bloc%20has%20released%20a%20joint%20statement%2C%20saying%20it%20stands%20with%20the%20media.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Indian%20National%20Developmental%20Inclusive%20Alliance%20(INDIA)%20parties%20strongly%20condemn%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janta%20Party%20(BJP)%20government's%20fresh%20attack%20on%20the%20media.%20We%20steadfastly%20stand%20with%20the%20media%20and%20for%20the%20constitutionally%20protected%20freedoms%20of%20speech%20and%20expression%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bloc%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndividually%2C%20prominent%20Opposition%20leaders%2C%20Congress's%20Shashi%20Tharor%2C%20JDU's%20Rajiv%20Ranjan%20Singh%2C%20RJD's%20Manoj%20Jha%20and%20Shiv%20Sena%20(UBT)'s%20Priyanka%20Chaturvedi%20targeted%20the%20government%20over%20the%20raids.%20Many%20of%20them%20also%20cited%20India's%20poor%20ranking%20on%20World%20Press%20Freedom%20index.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696333260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2F5vrjp80o_newsclick_625x300_03_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnewsclick-raids-5-cities-100-sites-500-cops-how-delhi-police-planned-newsclick-raids-4445886%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20raids%20at%20homes%20of%20several%20journalists%20linked%20to%20NewsClick%20website%20this%20morning%20followed%20detailed%20planning%20and%20extensive%20coordination%20between%20teams%20of%20Delhi%20Police%2C%20sources%20from%20the%20force%20have%