20equal%20opportunities%20for%20leadership%20at%20all%20levels%20of%20decision-making%20in%20political%2C%20economic%2C%20and%20public%20life.%20One%20of%20the%20major%20indicators%20of%20this%20target%20is%20the%20proportion%20of%20seats%20held%20by%20women%20in%20national%20parliaments%20and%20local%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20September%2020%2C%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20passed%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill%2C%2027%20years%20after%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Flok-sabha-passes-womens-reservation-bill%2Farticle67327458.ece%5C%22%3Ewas%20first%20introduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20unanimous%20support%20received%20in%20both%20Houses%20of%20Parliament%20for%20the%20Bill%2C%20which%20seeks%20to%20reserve%2033%25%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%2C%20underscores%20the%20potential%20impact%20of%20the%20Bill%20on%20improving%20women%E2%80%99s%20lives%20and%20their%20participation%20in%20public%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Freports%2Fglobal-gender-gap-report-2023%2Fin-full%2Fbenchmarking-gender-gaps-2023%2F%5C%22%3EGlobal%20Gender%20Gap%20Report%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20India%20stands%20at%20a%20low%2036.7%25%20on%20gender%20parity%20related%20to%20%E2%80%98economic%20participation%20and%20opportunity.%E2%80%99%20Despite%20achieving%20parity%20in%20enrollment%20across%20all%20levels%20of%20education%2C%20the%20same%20cannot%20be%20said%20for%20gender%20parity%20in%20health%20and%20survival.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20ranks%20142%20out%20of%20146%20countries%20on%20the%20health%20and%20survival%20sub-index.%20India%20also%20performs%20poorly%20on%20the%20political%20empowerment%20sub-index.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Bill%20is%20significant%2C%20given%20that%20the%20share%20of%20women%20parliamentarians%20has%20never%20crossed%20the%2015%25%20mark%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%2070-year-old%20electoral%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Flok-sabha-passes-womens-reservation-bill-amit-shah-implementation-2029%5C%22%3ELok%20Sabha%20Passes%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill%2C%20Amit%20Shah%20Confirms%20Implementation%20Not%20Before%202029%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20India%20compare%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20on%20political%20empowerment%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20(UN)%2C%20as%20of%20January%201%2C%202023%2C%20women%20hold%20executive%20positions%20in%2031%20nations%2C%20and%20in%2034%20nations%2C%20women%20hold%20the%20titles%20of%20Head%20of%20State%20or%20Head%20of%20Government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww3.weforum.org%2Fdocs%2FWEF_GGGR_2023.pdf%5C%22%3EThe%20Global%20Gender%20Gap%20Index%20(GCCI)%20for%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20highlights%20the%20largest%20gender%20gap%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98Political%20Empowerment%E2%80%99%20sub-index%2C%20with%20only%2022.1%25%20of%20the%20gap%20closed%20and%20a%20significant%20variation%20in%20scores%20among%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20countries%20using%20reservation%20quotas%2C%20Rwanda%20leads%20with%20the%20highest%20percentage%20of%20women%20in%20its%20national%20legislative%20chamber%2C%20where%20women%20hold%2061.3%25%20of%20the%20seats.%20Cuba%20and%20Nicaragua%20follow%20closely%20at%2055.7%25%20and%2051.7%25%2C%20respectively.%20In%20contrast%2C%20India%20has%20achieved%2025.3%25%20parity%20in%20the%20political%20empowerment%20sub-indicator%2C%20with%20women%20representing%20only%2015.1%25%20of%20parliamentarians.%20While%20this%20marks%20the%20highest%20level%20for%20India%20since%20the%20inaugural%202006%20edition%20of%20GGGI%2C%20it%20is%20disconcerting%20to%20note%20that%2C%20at%20the%20current%20rate%20of%20progress%20from%202006%20to%202023%2C%20achieving%20political%20empowerment%20for%20women%20in%20India%20remains%20a%20distant%20dream%20for%20another%20162%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20context%2C%20the%20Bill%20holds%20great%20promise%20for%20promoting%20gender%20equality%20and%20women%E2%80%99s%20empowerment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20are%20several%20challenges%20in%20this%20Bill.%20There%20is%20no%20linear%20pathway%20from%20having%20reserved%20quotas%20for%20women%20to%20achieving%20political%20decision-making%20and%20empowerment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20analysis%20aims%20to%20address%20the%20complexities%20of%20reserved%20quotas%20and%20the%20gendered%20dimensions%20of%20ministerial%20portfolios%20held.%20It%20will%20also%20cover%20the%20significant%20barriers%20faced%20by%20women%20in%20politics%20including%20the%20question%20of%20intersectionality%20and%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fretracing-a-history-the-antecedents-of-the-womens-reservation-bill%5C%22%3EThe%20Women%20of%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20problem%20with%20reserved%20quotas%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20advocates%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fretracing-a-history-the-antecedents-of-the-womens-reservation-bill%5C%22%3Eargue%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20gender%20quotas%20can%20hinder%20women%E2%80%99s%20political%20empowerment%20by%20implying%20that%20they%20cannot%20succeed%20without%20special%20provisions.%20Concerns%20also%20exist%20about%20quotas%20diverting%20attention%20from%20the%20representation%20of%20other%20minority%20groups%2C%20potentially%20leading%20to%20similar%20demands%20for%20quotas%20from%20other%20marginalised%20communities.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20in%20India%2C%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill%20faces%20challenges%20related%20to%20both%20horizontal%20and%20vertical%20reservations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHorizontal%20reservation%20reserves%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20parliament%2C%20emphasising%20gender%20equity%20and%20gender-conscious%20policymaking.%20Vertical%20reservation%2C%20specifically%20for%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20within%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20quota%2C%20raises%20concerns%20about%20the%20representation%20of%20marginalised%20communities%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Flok-sabha-passes-womens-reservation-bill%2Farticle67327458.ece%5C%22%3Ewas%20observed%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20demands%20raised%20by%20opposition%20parties%20for%20a%20separate%20OBC%20sub-quota%20within%20the%20reserved%20quota%20for%20women.%20They%20argue%20that%20OBCs%20constitute%20nearly%2040%25%20of%20the%20population%2C%20but%20unlike%20Scheduled%20Castes%20(SCs)%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(STs)%2C%20they%20have%20no%20separate%20reservation%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%20assemblies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Futtar-pradesh-upper-caste-obc-woman-reservation-election-mp-mla%5C%22%3Erecent%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%3Cem%3E%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20highlighted%20how%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20largest%20state%20legislature%20in%20the%20country%2C%20has%20elected%20more%20women%20from%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20castes%20as%20MLAs%20and%20MPs%20compared%20to%20OBCs%2C%20who%20are%20numerically%20more%20dominant.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20while%20gender%20quotas%20can%20be%20a%20tool%20for%20achieving%20representation%2C%20they%20come%20with%20complexities%20and%20potential%20unintended%20consequences%20that%20require%20careful%20consideration.%20The%20question%20of%20intersectionalities%20in%20a%20caste-ridden%20society%20cannot%20be%20overlooked%2C%20and%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill%20should%20not%20end%20up%20disproportionately%20privileging%20upper-caste%20urban%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20is%20political%20representation%20not%20enough%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20guarantees%20women%E2%80%99s%20representation%20in%20politics%2C%20but%20the%20challenge%20lies%20in%20establishing%20institutional%20arrangements%20that%20enable%20women%20to%20act%20independently%2C%20avoiding%20tokenism%20and%20patriarchal%20patronage.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESocietal%20norms%20still%20pose%20significant%20obstacles%20to%20women%E2%80%99s%20effective%20participation%2C%20with%20barriers%20like%20limited%20access%20to%20education%2C%20lack%20of%20childcare%20support%2C%20and%20financial%20constraints.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDiscriminatory%20tactics%20by%20political%20parties%2C%20voter%20and%20party%20leader%20bias%20against%20women%2C%20and%20concerns%20about%20female%20candidates%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98electability%E2%80%99%20also%20persist.%20While%20the%20Bill%20shifts%20demand-side%20barriers%20in%20favour%20of%20women%20candidates%2C%20ensuring%20effective%20participation%20with%20the%20newly%20created%20critical%20mass%20of%20women%20in%20parliament%20is%20a%20challenge%2C%20given%20the%20lack%20of%20political%20education%20among%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20the%20additional%20problem%20of%20gender%20stereotypes%20that%20influence%20portfolio%20allocations%2C%20hindering%20women%20from%20holding%20key%20roles.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipu.org%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2F2023-03%2Fwomen-in-power-in-2023-new-data-shows-progress-wide-regional-gaps%5C%22%3EInter-Parliamentary%20Union%20(IPU)%202023%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20women%20have%20high%20representation%20in%20portfolios%20like%20women%20and%20gender%20equality%2C%20family%20and%20children%20affairs%2C%20social%20inclusion%20and%20development%2C%20indigenous%20and%20minority%20affairs.%20However%2C%20critical%20policy%20areas%20such%20as%20economic%2C%20defence%2C%20justice%2C%20and%20home%20affairs%20are%20dominated%20by%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F24175237%2FIMG_3927.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F24175237%2FIMG_3927.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F24175237%2FIMG_3927-300x120.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F24175237%2FIMG_3927-1024x410.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-542308%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolitical%20violence%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrsreports.congress.gov%2Fproduct%2Fpdf%2FR%2FR45483%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Political%20Violence%20Targeting%20Women%2C%20women%20candidates%20for%20office%20globally%20experience%20up%20to%208%25%20violence%2C%20while%20female%20politicians%20experience%2012%25.%20Political%20party%20supporters%20face%2024%25%20violence%2C%20women%20voters%202%25%2C%20and%20government%20officials%20experience%2016%25%20of%20political%20violence%20attacks.%20Activists%2C%20human%20rights%20defenders%2C%20and%20social%20leaders%20experience%20the%20highest%20violence%2C%20accounting%20for%2038%25%20of%20political%20violence%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20the%20study%20notes%20that%20data%20on%20violence%20targeting%20women%20in%20politics%20are%20restricted%20to%20acts%20of%20physical%20violence%20against%20women%20in%20public%20settings%20during%20their%20engagement%20in%20the%20political%20process.%20It%20does%20not%20include%20acts%20of%20bullying%20or%20intimidation%2C%20cases%20of%20domestic%20violence%2C%20or%20virtual%20aggressive%20actions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unwomen.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FHeadquarters%2FAttachments%2FSections%2FLibrary%2FPublications%2F2014%2FViolence%2520Against%2520Women%2520in%2520Politics-Report.pdf%5C%22%3EUN%20Women%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Violence%20against%20Women%20in%20Politics%20highlights%20how%20women%20who%20participate%20in%20politics%20and%20public%20life%20are%20perceived%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20male%20superior%20status%2C%20resulting%20in%20violence%20against%20them.%20This%20serves%20as%20a%20significant%20barrier%20for%20women%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20the%20political%20process.%20It%20must%20also%20be%20noted%20that%20men%20with%20registered%20records%20of%20violence%20against%20women%20(as%20well%20as%20other%20types%20of%20criminal%20offences)%20are%20allowed%20to%20participate%20in%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20regard%2C%20it%20is%20disturbing%20to%20note%20that%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadrindia.org%2Fcontent%2F%25E2%2580%2598134-mps-mlas-have-cases-crime-against-women%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Association%20of%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%20revealed%20that%20a%20total%20of%20113%20MLAs%20and%2021%20MPs%20have%20declared%20cases%20of%20crimes%20against%20women%2C%20with%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20leading%20the%20statistics%20followed%20by%20the%20Congress%20party.%20Such%20statistics%20demand%20stringent%20measures%20to%20be%20adopted%20toward%20the%20decriminalisation%20of%20politics%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Nari%20Shakti%20Vandana%20Adhiniyam%20Bill%20represents%20a%20crucial%20step%20towards%20enhancing%20women%E2%80%99s%20political%20representation%20in%20India.%20Quotas%20for%20women%20have%20been%20shown%20to%20improve%20public%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fopinion%2Fwomen-s-reservation-bill-will-bridge-the-gender-gap-in-political-decision-making-in-india%2Fstory-DrJt5apRR5J9UoqeB3CXHO.html%5C%22%3Espending%20on%20services%20that%20matter%20to%20them%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20drinking%20water%2C%20sanitation%2C%20public%20health%2C%20primary%20education%2C%20and%20roads%2C%20as%20demonstrated%20in%20the%20case%20of%20gram%20panchayats.%20Studies%20have%20also%20indicated%20that%20a%20higher%20representation%20of%20women%20in%20parliament%20leads%20to%20the%20passing%20of%20more%20gender-sensitive%20laws%20on%20issues%20like%20sexual%20harassment%2C%20rape%2C%20and%20domestic%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20local%20female%20leaders%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20advocate%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarnegieendowment.org%2F2023%2F09%2F26%2Findia-s-new-gender-quota-law-is-win-for-women-mostly-pub-90644%5C%22%3Egender-equal%20property%20inheritance%20laws%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Bill%2C%20by%20itself%2C%20cannot%20achieve%20significant%20progress%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20empowerment%20unless%20efforts%20are%20made%20to%20address%20deep-rooted%20patriarchal%20norms%20that%20assign%20women%20low%20status%20in%20society%2C%20keep%20them%20out%20of%20the%20labour%20force%2C%20burden%20them%20disproportionately%20with%20unpaid%20domestic%20and%20care%20work%2C%20and%20use%20violence%20as%20a%20means%20of%20repression%20or%20discipline.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20passage%20of%20the%20Bill%20is%20a%20beacon%20of%20hope%2C%20but%20realising%20its%20full%20potential%20requires%20concerted%20efforts%20to%20overcome%20these%20hurdles%20and%20create%20a%20more%20inclusive%20and%20equitable%20political%20landscape%20for%20women%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDivya%20Pradeep%20and%20Roopa%20Patavardhan%20teach%20Economics%20at%20Christ%20University%2C%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696331715000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F261